This article summarizes the reactions of several mayors to President Obama's fiscal policy speech. The mayors express support for the President's emphasis on long-term fiscal responsibility and shared prosperity. They believe that a leaner, more efficient government is necessary, but cutting at any cost is not the solution. The mayors appreciate the President's commitment to reducing the deficit while protecting the middle class and making smart investments for the future. They also highlight the importance of investing in education, healthcare, and infrastructure to ensure America's competitiveness in the global economy. The mayors commend the President for his balanced approach and urge Congress to consider his proposals seriously.